explain select a, b, count(1) over(partition by a) from t2;
Query Plan
====================================================
|ID|OPERATOR             |NAME    |EST. ROWS|COST  |
----------------------------------------------------
|0 |WINDOW FUNCTION      |        |200000   |556716|
|1 | SORT                |        |200000   |518514|
|2 |  EXCHANGE IN DISTR  |        |200000   |80792 |
|3 |   EXCHANGE OUT DISTR|:EX10000|200000   |61860 |
|4 |    GRANULE ITERATOR |        |200000   |61860 |
|5 |     TABLE SCAN      |t2      |200000   |61860 |
====================================================

